{
  "card_id": "midweek_reversal",
  "type": "merged_concept",
  "canonical_term": "Midweek Reversal",
  "aliases": [
    "Wednesday Reversal",
    "wednesday reversal",
    "周中反转"
  ],
  "school": "ICT",
  "definition": "A weekly profile where Monday and Tuesday move opposite the weekly bias to form the weekly candle's wick, Wednesday prints a candle-2 closure or reversal candle confirmed by an hourly change in state of delivery, and Thursday-Friday expand in the intended direction.",
  "identification_rules": [
    "Monday and Tuesday close opposing the anticipated weekly bias, creating the wick portion of the weekly candle.",
    "On Wednesday, look for a candle-2 closure or reversal candle that sweeps the prior extreme and closes back inside the weekly range.",
    "Drop to the hourly time frame within Wednesday's candle and verify a change in state of delivery confirming the daily high/low.",
    "Treat the confirmed Wednesday extreme as the weekly wick high/low to trade away from on Thursday and Friday.",
    "Plan expansion entries on Thursday and Friday (candle 3 and candle 4 of the fractal model) toward higher-time-frame objectives."
  ],
  "trading_implication": "The midweek reversal frames Thursday and Friday as the primary expansion days, allowing traders to align lower-time-frame entries with the weekly bias once Wednesday confirms. Traders can either take the candle-2 entry on Wednesday after the hourly CISD or wait for continuation on Thursday/Friday. Targets are projected to the average daily range or a higher-time-frame objective. Monday and Tuesday counter-bias action is expected and forms the weekly wick rather than invalidating the bias.",
  "common_mistakes": [
    "Treating Monday/Tuesday opposing moves as a change in weekly bias rather than wick formation.",
    "Trading the Wednesday reversal without verifying an hourly change in state of delivery inside the candle.",
    "Entering on Wednesday's sweep before a candle-2 closure confirms, when waiting another day is required.",
    "未等待周四明确的反转确认就提前在周三低点附近建仓",
    "忽视经济日历中的高影响新闻事件，导致周中被新闻打破形态",
    "将周中反转与单纯的低点混淆，忽视Change in the state of delivery的确认"
  ],
  "related_concepts": [],
  "merge_strategy": "llm_synthesis",
  "merge_model": "deepseek/deepseek-chat",
  "merge_notes": "School conflict: first card says 'Price Action', second says 'ICT'; picked ICT by majority (1 vs 1, but ICT is more specific). First card's definition is in Chinese and less precise; second card's definition used as it is more operational. First card's identification rules are less specific; second card's rules used. Common mistakes from both cards merged.",
